Rogers v. City of Buffalo et al. (Supreme Court, General Term, Fifth Department. January 11, 1889.) Appeal from specie 1 term, Brie county. This is an appeal in the case of Rogers v. City of Buffalo, ante, 671.

Argued before Barker, P. J., and Haight, Bradley, and Dwight, JJ.

Wm. F. Sheehan, lor appellant. Frederic Atony, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Judgment affirmed, without costs to either party. All concur, except Haight, J., not voting.
